    <text>
      <body>
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>British Museum</placeName>
                    <date>15 March 1860</date>
                    <salute>My dear Henslow,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                  <p>I have signed the Deed appointing me your co-trustee in the settlement of worthy John Brown’s testamentary affairs; and trust I may have no unexpected reason to repent the step—To have you for a co-adjutor was my chief ground for taking it.</p>
                  <p>I return M. <hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Laing’s letter, and have written to him to say that I am prepared to add my signature to any Trust-document or receipt which bears your’s: and I suppose that this is really what is requisite to work the machinery for winding up the affairs.</p>
                  <p>Believe me, |Dear Henslow, |Ever truly yours, | R. <hi rend="superscript">d</hi> Owen.</p>
                  <p>I send by this Post a description of some odd African fossils, which I imagine may seem to D <hi rend="superscript">n</hi> to be one of the steps from the Crocodile to the Cat!</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
